 Time Complexity
1. createAccount()
You traverse to the end of the linked list to insert a new node.
Worst case: list has n accounts
 Time Complexity: O(n)

2. displayAccounts()
You traverse the entire list to print all accounts.

 Time Complexity: O(n)

3. searchAccount(int id)
Linear search through the list.

 Time Complexity: O(n)

4. deposit()
Calls searchAccount()

 Time Complexity: O(n)

5. withdraw()
Calls searchAccount()

 Time Complexity: O(n)

6. deleteAccount()
You may traverse the list to find the node.

 Time Complexity: O(n)

7. Main Menu Loop
Runs k times (user-dependent)
Each operation inside is at most O(n)

 Overall: O(k × n)

Space Complexity
Each account is stored as a node in the linked list.
If there are n accounts, you store n nodes.

 Space Complexity: O(n)

No extra significant memory (no arrays, recursion, etc.)
 Summary Table
Operation	Time Complexity
Create Account	O(n)
